stylometry: The tradeoff you must balance when deciding how much inventory to order is do you want to order alot of inventory and take a chance of having wasted inventory or order just enough inventory to meet the demand.  EOQ basically means that a company makes sure they never run out of inventory.  Its the most basic of the inventory models and the price of the product from the supplier is always constant.  The tradeoff of EOQ is do you want to order more less frequently or order less more frequently.  Things to think about when doing so are:  Will products soil, do prices change seasonally, and a problem could be that it may take up storage space.
